narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about various techniques and current ideas in cell biology. I improved my ability to read papers carefully and critically.
paper reading and analyzing skills also learn how to present data and writing mini reviews
How to read papers more critically
I learned how to critically analyze papers and improved my skills in sharing my ideas during discussions.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I would have been more engaged in the class if we had the opportunities to pick our own papers (perhaps in consultation with the professor). In general, I like the discussion format, but it would be nice if one of us, rather than a professor, led the discussion.
strength: reading paper in different areas, largely increased my knowledge
I like the size of this discussion section. It helped with the exchange of ideas
This is well organized and the discussion is always interesting.
The strength of the course is that it gives us the opportunities of sharing our ideas and helps us improve our critical thoughts

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would recommend this course because I believe I learned a lot. I would also tell the student that the course requires read papers every week, so it is crucial to have time in the schedule to do it.
Yes. it is a great course if you want to practice reading paper and discussing with others.
